	   <tr><td colspan=2>I propose that a clearer comment is that we have a tremendous variety of aggro management tools, ranging from wide weapon choices to&nbsp;&nbsp;different kinds of spells.<br><br>I can normally help manage aggro in any fight, either increasing it for the MA or taking it myself.  My taunt is maxed and OK, but it's the diversity of our tools that lets us manage aggro.<br><br>I'm PROUD of the fact that when we have a warrior MA (my preference!) I deal a LOT of damage and usually never need a heal during the entire raid.  But if a mob turns on a chanter I can use 2 Spears (Pain &amp; Plague) and a HT to slam the beastie for over 1200 HP in 1.5 seconds and get it very, very mad at me to save the chanter, then whomp it until the MA is ready to take an aggro transfer, and FD or HS to let him take it.<br><br>It's not about claiming we can out-taunt other toons, it's using the cool mix of tools we have.<br><br>Cirulik Silvertongue<br>54th Iksar Reaver<br>&nbsp;<br>Cirulik Silvertongue<br>64th Grave Lord of Greenmist<br></td></tr>
